data.title: DONALD DUCK "THE DOGNAPPER" FRAMED PRODUCTION DRAWING SIGNED BY ARTIST MILT KAHL.

data.text:

Thank you for visiting our past auction results. If you have an identical (or similar) to this auction item, please call or contact us to discuss. We look forward to speaking with you.

Item Description

14.75x17.25" frame contains sheet of animation paper that has been professionally double-matted to 8.5x11" and shows full body image of long-billed Donald Duck dressed in policeman's uniform in lead pencil (w/red pencil accents) from the 1934 Mickey Mouse cartoon "The Dognappers." Art has been signed one of Disney's Nine Old Men - Milt Kahl (1909-1987), who added "Best Wishes," inscription. Art some minor pencil smudging but remains VF and ready for display. Great early Donald Duck art.
